(KEYPAD BEEPING)

00:32.631 --> 00:34.700
911. What is your emergency?

00:34.701 --> 00:39.638
I'm at the gas station on Aspen
Hill, and a man just fell.

00:39.639 --> 00:42.173
I think someone's been hurt
in our parking lot, a lady.

00:42.174 --> 00:45.477
Where's the person at now?
She's laying in the parking lot, sir.

00:45.478 --> 00:46.512
(SIREN WAILING)

00:46.513 --> 00:48.112
What's going on there?

00:48.113 --> 00:50.882
I think this guy's lawn mower
fell on him or something, man.

00:50.883 --> 00:53.918
Like, it sliced him up maybe.
I don't know.

00:53.919 --> 00:55.487
(WOMAN CRYING)

00:55.488 --> 00:57.523
Oh, my God!

00:57.524 --> 00:59.758
A man has been killed
in front of me!

00:59.759 --> 01:01.993
Oh, God!
Ma'am, calm down.

01:01.994 --> 01:05.664
How did he die, ma'am?
I don't know?

01:05.665 --> 01:06.931
I don't know?

01:06.932 --> 01:08.166
Reporting deadly news:

01:08.167 --> 01:11.570
a bizarre shooting spree in Maryland
has led to a statewide manhunt.

01:11.571 --> 01:13.839
The police have no confirmation
whether the shooting...

01:13.840 --> 01:17.909
A violent rampage ravaging
the Washington, D.C., area,

01:17.910 --> 01:19.745
bringing the total number
of victims to seven.

01:19.746 --> 01:24.483
They all appear to be random victims.
Don't appear to be anyone's enemy.

01:24.484 --> 01:28.621
Don't appear to be involved
in anything coordinated,

01:28.622 --> 01:31.523
just simply random targets,
innocent people.

01:31.524 --> 01:34.760
Aspen Hill City Police.
This line is recorded.

01:34.761 --> 01:37.563
Good morning.
Don't say anything. Just listen.

01:37.564 --> 01:40.733
We're the people that are causing
the killings in your area.

01:40.734 --> 01:44.470
We've called you three times before
to try to set up negotiations.

01:44.471 --> 01:46.938
We got no response.
People have died.

01:46.939 --> 01:47.939
(CLICK)

01:47.940 --> 01:49.575
(DIAL TONE BEEPING)

01:49.576 --> 01:52.110
The search continues for the
man and men responsible

01:52.111 --> 01:55.414
for the seemingly random
shootings across the D.C. area.

01:55.415 --> 01:58.283
Authorities now suggest that the
killers may be traveling in a...

01:58.284 --> 02:01.387
You need to send an ambulance.
A woman was cleaning a car...

02:01.388 --> 02:02.454
(SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

02:02.455 --> 02:04.757
This woman was just hurt!
She's bleeding from everywhere!

02:04.758 --> 02:07.058
I can't do nothing for her!
Could it have been a gunshot?

02:07.059 --> 02:08.993
Now saying that they
believe the sniper

02:08.994 --> 02:12.263
is likely to be working
with an accomplice.

02:12.264 --> 02:14.600
To look out for a
1990 Chevy Caprice

02:14.601 --> 02:17.101
with a New Jersey
license plate number.

02:17.102 --> 02:20.706
They have taken two men into custody
in connection with the sniper case.

02:20.707 --> 02:24.142
It appears that the men were sound
asleep inside their car at a rest area.

02:24.143 --> 02:26.010
Maryland residents can
rest easy tonight,

02:26.011 --> 02:30.014
knowing that the killers who terrorized
the suburbs of Washington, D.C.,

02:30.015 --> 02:32.118
are now behind bars.

02:39.158 --> 02:42.263
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

02:51.036 --> 02:54.141
(CHIRPING CONTINUES)

03:39.386 --> 03:41.121
You stop that now.

03:43.656 --> 03:47.225
That's enough!
You know that's the way it go.

03:47.226 --> 03:50.131
You want to eat,
I'm gonna have to work.

03:53.198 --> 03:56.635
I'm gonna come for you
as soon as I can.

03:56.636 --> 03:58.871
You want to be a
spoiled child, then?

03:58.872 --> 04:01.477
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

04:10.884 --> 04:11.985
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

04:13.019 --> 04:15.189
(ENGINE REVVING)

04:34.741 --> 04:38.080
(BELLS TOLLING)

04:49.456 --> 04:50.925
(BELL RINGS)

04:52.826 --> 04:55.360
Please, Papa, can I have one?
One what? I didn't get anything.

04:55.361 --> 04:57.029
Yes, you did!

04:57.030 --> 04:58.030
(LAUGHING)
Oh.

04:58.031 --> 04:59.331
We saw you!
Oh, did you?

04:59.332 --> 05:00.332
Yes!

05:00.333 --> 05:01.635
Hmm, let's see.

05:03.036 --> 05:04.137
Oh!

05:05.738 --> 05:08.440
Thank you.
And one for my princess.

05:08.441 --> 05:10.143
Thanks.
Come on.

05:12.112 --> 05:14.713
(GIRL SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

05:14.714 --> 05:17.886
Tomorrow when I wake up, I'm just
gonna look like a little circle candy.

05:24.691 --> 05:27.796
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

05:49.082 --> 05:52.084
(CHIRPING CONTINUES)

05:52.085 --> 05:55.492
(SUBDUED ETHEREAL MUSIC)

06:45.305 --> 06:46.772
<i>♪ We'll catch a fox
and put it in a box ♪</i>

06:46.773 --> 06:49.043
<i>♪ And then we'll let him go ♪</i>

06:50.242 --> 06:52.010
<i>♪ A-hunting we will go ♪</i>

06:52.011 --> 06:54.046
<i>♪ We'll catch a cat
and put it in a hat ♪</i>

06:54.047 --> 06:55.981
I'm hungry.
You're hungry?

06:55.982 --> 06:57.516
Yeah.
Oh, okay.

06:57.517 --> 06:59.451
Are you hungry too?
Not really.

06:59.452 --> 07:02.087
Uh, I'm hungry too.

07:02.088 --> 07:04.258
(DOG BARKING)

07:12.198 --> 07:14.533
How far is it?
We're almost there.

07:14.534 --> 07:16.504
I'm tired of walking.

07:17.437 --> 07:20.542
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

07:21.774 --> 07:24.879
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

07:42.996 --> 07:46.565
(LAUGHTER)

07:46.566 --> 07:49.671
(WAVES CRASHING)

07:55.508 --> 07:57.845
Is that boy following us?

08:03.750 --> 08:06.822
(SOLEMN WOODWIND MUSIC)

08:46.726 --> 08:48.963
(COUGHING)

08:50.663 --> 08:51.897
You all right?

08:51.898 --> 08:53.333
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

08:53.334 --> 08:54.803
Hey.

08:57.070 --> 08:58.103
You okay?

08:58.104 --> 09:00.207
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

09:03.009 --> 09:04.976
Come on.

09:04.977 --> 09:06.513
(COUGHING)

09:17.190 --> 09:20.295
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

09:30.002 --> 09:33.542
Is that boy gonna
stay with us, Papa?

09:34.741 --> 09:37.409
(SIGHS)
Maybe, baby.

09:37.410 --> 09:39.811
Maybe. Hey, lay down.

09:39.812 --> 09:40.913
(GRUNTS)

09:42.515 --> 09:45.250
When is Mama coming?

09:45.251 --> 09:48.487
Mama's not coming.
Why not?

09:48.988 --> 09:51.423
Hey.

09:51.424 --> 09:55.427
You guys are on a special
vacation with Papa, remember?

09:55.428 --> 09:59.231
And if you saw Mama, then you
wouldn't see Papa anymore.

09:59.232 --> 10:00.499
Why?

10:00.500 --> 10:02.734
Don't worry about it.

10:02.735 --> 10:04.536
Okay?

10:04.537 --> 10:07.639
Is that what you want? You
want Papa to get in trouble?

10:07.640 --> 10:08.740
No.
Hmm?

10:08.741 --> 10:11.243
No.
Leave my papa alone!

10:11.244 --> 10:14.713
Leave my papa alone.
That's right, baby.

10:14.714 --> 10:15.981
(SMOOCHING)

10:15.982 --> 10:17.516
(LAUGHTER)

10:17.517 --> 10:20.285
Mmwah!
(LAUGHS)

10:20.286 --> 10:21.586
Okay, lights out.

10:21.587 --> 10:23.622
(CHILDREN GIGGLE)

10:23.623 --> 10:24.724
Night.

10:26.058 --> 10:27.326
(SIGHS)

10:27.327 --> 10:29.764
Oh, boy, sorry about that.

10:33.599 --> 10:35.034
(SIGHS)

10:41.442 --> 10:44.576
So has your mother

10:44.577 --> 10:47.512
done this before?

10:47.513 --> 10:49.616
She always leave.

10:52.151 --> 10:53.587
And you don't have anybody else?

11:00.793 --> 11:03.030
What are we gonna
do with you, huh?

11:11.604 --> 11:15.441
(SERENE STRING MUSIC)

11:15.442 --> 11:17.512
(CHILDREN SHOUTING)

11:29.755 --> 11:32.860
(SHOUTING)

11:35.027 --> 11:36.161
(BEEP)

11:36.162 --> 11:40.966
Mama, me did write you one letter,
but I didn't know where to send it,

11:40.967 --> 11:42.670
so me burn it up.

11:44.505 --> 11:48.341
If you come home, you're
not gonna find me here.

11:48.342 --> 11:49.977
I am somewhere else now.

11:52.879 --> 11:56.715
The man up the road,
do you know him?

11:56.716 --> 11:59.150
I met him in autumn.

11:59.151 --> 12:02.355
He let me stay and work for him.

12:02.356 --> 12:04.459
Me get a job now.

12:08.794 --> 12:13.166
The other tourist, him
gone, but him still there.

12:17.136 --> 12:19.070
He is American.

12:19.071 --> 12:22.341
He teaches me to talk
like an American.

12:22.342 --> 12:24.846
He says I can be an American too.

12:28.781 --> 12:31.249
Him name John.

12:31.250 --> 12:32.351
(PHONE LINE CLICKS)

12:42.628 --> 12:44.665
(CHILDREN SHOUTING)

12:51.405 --> 12:53.207
What state do you live in?

12:54.774 --> 12:56.076
Washington.

12:57.643 --> 12:58.911
There are two.

13:00.314 --> 13:04.384
Well, one's the capital and...
the other one's just a place.

13:05.885 --> 13:07.555
Which one's yours?

13:08.921 --> 13:10.691
Just the place.

13:15.861 --> 13:18.966
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

13:22.603 --> 13:25.804
She not coming back, is she?

13:25.805 --> 13:26.973
I don't know.

13:29.208 --> 13:34.413
When I was your age, I used to play
a game called "life is not fair."

13:34.414 --> 13:35.883
You know why they called it that?

13:38.385 --> 13:40.553
'Cause life is not fair.

13:40.554 --> 13:44.458
It sucks, but you got to play.

13:48.794 --> 13:51.464
I don't know, maybe...

13:51.465 --> 13:53.865
she wants to come back,

13:53.866 --> 13:55.934
but she can't.

13:55.935 --> 13:58.105
Maybe she's dead.

14:04.777 --> 14:07.882
(CHILDREN SHOUTING)

14:10.249 --> 14:11.552
What'd you say?

14:13.520 --> 14:14.955
Hope she is.

14:19.925 --> 14:22.761
(AIRPLANE ENGINE ROARING)

14:22.762 --> 14:26.168
(SWAGGERING BRASS MUSIC)

14:30.102 --> 14:32.272
(BELL RINGING)

14:38.778 --> 14:41.813
Hey, stranger. Welcome back.

14:41.814 --> 14:42.914
And who's this now?

14:42.915 --> 14:45.250
That's my son.
That's not your son.

14:45.251 --> 14:48.421
That's my other son. Are you okay?

14:48.422 --> 14:51.022
Sure, sure. Just busy, busy, busy.

14:51.023 --> 14:54.593
Did I leave a shirt here?
A blue one?

14:54.594 --> 14:56.928
Maybe.
Yeah?

14:56.929 --> 14:59.030
Check.

14:59.031 --> 15:02.135
Well, let me go wash up quick.
You guys can say hello.

15:04.504 --> 15:05.973
(SIGHS)

15:25.024 --> 15:28.063
So, uh, visiting your dad?

15:32.031 --> 15:34.500
Hey. Is it okay if
we stay tonight?

15:34.501 --> 15:35.668
(LAUGHS)

15:35.669 --> 15:39.338
Why didn't you tell me about him?

15:39.339 --> 15:40.507
(MOANS)

15:42.975 --> 15:47.114
I'm not gonna catch him going through my
underwear drawers or something, am I?

15:50.317 --> 15:51.384
Hey.

15:53.320 --> 15:55.322
Can I get you to go
out for a little bit?

15:58.057 --> 16:00.225
Don't get lost.

16:00.226 --> 16:01.796
Okay.

16:30.657 --> 16:33.762
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

16:46.540 --> 16:47.740
May I take your order?

16:47.741 --> 16:51.610
(SIREN WAILING FAINTLY)

16:51.611 --> 16:54.145
Do you have cheap burgers?

16:54.146 --> 16:55.247
(CLICK)

17:07.828 --> 17:09.160
(DOOR OPENS, BELL RINGS)

17:09.161 --> 17:11.162
Change your whole life
if you're ready, sir.

17:11.163 --> 17:14.165
The United States Army is hiring.
Yes, you sir.

17:14.165 --> 17:16.904
(SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

17:17.002 --> 17:18.237
(CAR ALARM BEEPS)

17:22.709 --> 17:26.044
You got a minute for
your future, son?

17:26.045 --> 17:28.012
How old are you?

17:28.012 --> 17:30.215
16.

17:30.216 --> 17:33.918
Listen, you're a little bit too young, but
you come back in a year, you understand?

17:33.919 --> 17:37.590
You come back.
We'll be ready for you.

17:37.591 --> 17:39.090
Have yourself a good day.

17:39.091 --> 17:41.061
Change your whole life
if you're ready, sir.

17:44.497 --> 17:48.638
(MUFFLED RAP MUSIC PLAYING)

18:04.950 --> 18:07.053
(ENGINE REVVING)

18:26.506 --> 18:27.640
Hop on.

18:27.641 --> 18:29.076
(ENGINE REVS)

18:31.243 --> 18:34.315
(TENSE INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

19:12.786 --> 19:15.219
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

19:15.220 --> 19:16.755
(DOG BARKING FAINTLY)

19:16.756 --> 19:20.062
(ENGINE SPUTTERS)

19:24.331 --> 19:25.331
(SIGHS)

19:25.332 --> 19:27.067
(ENGINE SPUTTERS WEAKLY)

19:31.270 --> 19:33.973
This used to be my
neighborhood, you know?

19:33.974 --> 19:37.543
I used to live here.
People used to live here.

19:37.544 --> 19:39.113
Real people, I thought.

19:44.083 --> 19:47.355
Everybody turned into ghosts.

19:49.322 --> 19:51.592
It was like I didn't exist anymore.

19:54.327 --> 19:56.363
Well, not everybody.

19:59.566 --> 20:02.266
Some of them turned
out to be vampires.

20:02.267 --> 20:04.703
Suck me dry.

20:04.704 --> 20:07.806
People I would've never expected.

20:07.807 --> 20:09.040
My wife.

20:09.041 --> 20:12.778
Just one day I woke up, and I don't
know how I didn't see it before.

20:12.779 --> 20:14.415
(CHUCKLES)

20:16.115 --> 20:19.653
It's evil. Real evil.

20:23.288 --> 20:27.961
There are some evil...
people in this world.

20:34.166 --> 20:36.035
Like here.

20:36.036 --> 20:40.104
The lady who lives here,
that's a real piece of shit.

20:40.105 --> 20:42.674
Testified against me in court.

20:42.675 --> 20:45.076
That's what they do.

20:45.077 --> 20:48.881
They take your kids away and
say that I kidnapped them.

20:48.882 --> 20:50.716
How can I kidnap my own kids?

20:50.717 --> 20:53.419
They're my kids.

20:53.420 --> 20:57.856
And then she just gets to live
here like nothing ever happened.

20:57.857 --> 21:01.495
The fucking vampire.
I hope she dies.

21:03.797 --> 21:06.965
Vampires can't die.

21:06.966 --> 21:10.403
They're already dead.
That's right.

21:10.904 --> 21:12.371
'Cause they aren't people.

21:12.372 --> 21:14.573
What kind of person breaks up
a family like that anyway?

21:14.574 --> 21:18.142
Just like the Army. They promise all
these things, then they take them away.

21:18.143 --> 21:20.646
It doesn't matter if you have
skills, something to offer.

21:20.647 --> 21:23.082
(DOGS BARKING)

21:23.083 --> 21:25.249
They just chew you up, expect
you to keep your head down

21:25.250 --> 21:27.052
and march right into
the slaughterhouse.

21:27.053 --> 21:30.154
Once you see what is happening,

21:30.155 --> 21:34.660
you've got to fight it.
It's insane not to fight it.

21:34.661 --> 21:35.694
(LAWN MOWER WHINING)

21:35.695 --> 21:37.429
Hit back.

21:37.430 --> 21:39.932
You give them the slaughterhouse.

21:40.433 --> 21:41.801
(LAWN MOWER STOPS)

21:46.072 --> 21:49.074
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

21:49.075 --> 21:52.147
(TENSE STRING MUSIC)

22:00.285 --> 22:03.390
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

22:38.223 --> 22:40.995
(MUSIC FADES)

22:44.497 --> 22:45.799
(TRUCK HORN BLARES)

22:49.536 --> 22:52.007
Well, what do we have here?

22:54.474 --> 22:57.208
Hey, man, we don't
want any trouble.

22:57.209 --> 23:01.849
Well, that's tough, cause
you are the fucking trouble.

23:04.951 --> 23:09.054
No trouble. Just a good-looking
black man running on a hot day.

23:09.055 --> 23:11.359
Like I said.

23:13.493 --> 23:16.028
(LAUGHING)

23:16.029 --> 23:18.163
When did you get back?
That's confidential.

23:18.164 --> 23:19.263
(LAUGHS)

23:19.264 --> 23:20.700
Hi. I'm Ray.

23:22.769 --> 23:24.503
Nice kid... a little too talkative.

23:24.504 --> 23:26.471
(LAUGHS)

23:26.472 --> 23:28.874
So I was about to go
blow off some steam.

23:28.875 --> 23:31.777
Care to join?
Absolutely.

23:31.778 --> 23:33.548
Hop in. You, in the back.

23:36.049 --> 23:37.184
(GRUNTS)

23:38.250 --> 23:40.251
(LAUGHS)

23:40.252 --> 23:42.355
(GUNSHOTS)

23:52.832 --> 23:55.167
See...

23:55.168 --> 23:58.203
I can't take her to court 'cause
I don't know where she is,

23:58.204 --> 24:01.506
not that the court would do any good.
They never give custody to the father.

24:01.507 --> 24:02.608
(SCOFFS)

24:06.079 --> 24:07.579
So what am I supposed to do?

24:07.580 --> 24:10.616
I don't know.
Pray for a earthquake,

24:11.117 --> 24:14.924
fucking bolt of lightning,
act of God, some shit.

24:16.055 --> 24:19.159
It's all you. Let's go.

24:33.573 --> 24:34.708
(GUNSHOT)

24:36.609 --> 24:38.946
(GUNSHOT)

24:41.114 --> 24:43.115
Kid's a fucking natural.

24:43.116 --> 24:45.784
How does that feel?
Pretty good, huh?

24:45.785 --> 24:47.588
Fucking letting her go?

24:48.955 --> 24:54.626
But if you really want to make
a difference in the world...

24:54.627 --> 24:59.668
you're gonna want to go...
with my old friend...

25:04.671 --> 25:06.975
the widow maker.

25:07.874 --> 25:10.979
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

25:17.050 --> 25:18.750
(LAUGHS)
Fuck a duck.

25:18.751 --> 25:20.886
It helps if you actually try
to hit the damn thing.

25:20.887 --> 25:23.488
Maybe I ought to
shoot at some birds.

25:23.489 --> 25:26.026
One of them will fly into
a bullet by accident.

25:28.094 --> 25:30.696
Want to try it?

25:30.697 --> 25:31.897
Easy now.

25:31.898 --> 25:33.501
Lady's got some kick.

25:45.678 --> 25:47.679
(GUNSHOT)

25:47.680 --> 25:51.351
All right, press it more
into your shoulder.

25:51.352 --> 25:54.052
All right, but with a light touch.

25:54.053 --> 25:55.321
Go slow.

26:11.104 --> 26:12.104
(GUNSHOT)

26:12.105 --> 26:13.672
Hah!

26:13.673 --> 26:15.810
I told you the kid was a natural.

26:21.948 --> 26:23.049
(GUNSHOT)

26:29.323 --> 26:30.558
You okay?

26:33.426 --> 26:35.727
Oh, come on, now. Please?

26:35.728 --> 26:38.130
I'm sorry. I can't.

26:38.131 --> 26:39.131
Why not?

26:39.132 --> 26:42.501
I mean, how does a voice
this sweet go so sour on me?

26:42.502 --> 26:43.635
(LAUGHS)

26:43.636 --> 26:47.407
I'll get in trouble.
Oh, please. Come on, please.

26:47.408 --> 26:51.109
There's a note in the file.
That says what?

26:51.110 --> 26:55.647
That says I can't give
out any information.

26:55.648 --> 26:57.649
(SIGHS)

26:57.650 --> 26:59.119
Are you married?

27:00.987 --> 27:02.389
Do you have kids?

27:04.290 --> 27:06.992
I don't think...
Oh, come on.

27:06.993 --> 27:09.328
Is it an emergency?

27:09.329 --> 27:10.430
It might be.

27:10.431 --> 27:12.631
Something terrible might happen.

27:12.632 --> 27:13.867
Hold on.

27:18.638 --> 27:20.071
(SIGHS)

27:20.072 --> 27:21.608
Here you go.

27:23.343 --> 27:24.377
Hello?

27:24.378 --> 27:25.811
Yes, hello. I'm here.

27:25.812 --> 27:28.046
They're not enrolled anymore.

27:28.047 --> 27:30.816
Yeah, I know that.

